#. <section class="sutta" id="sn11.19"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.19:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.19:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 19. Satthāravandanāsutta → dutiyasakkanamassanasuttaṃ (bj, s2, s3) | sakkanamassanasuttaṃ (2) (s1) | sakka-namassana (2) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn11.19:0.3"
msgid "19. Satthāravandanāsutta"
msgstr "19. Who Sakka Worships"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.235"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.19:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ jetavane."
msgstr "Near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove."

msgctxt "sn11.19:1.2"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo mātaliṃ saṅgāhakaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his "
"charioteer Mātali:"

msgctxt "sn11.19:1.3"
msgid ""
"‘yojehi, samma mātali, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ, uyyānabhūmiṃ gacchāma "
"subhūmiṃ dassanāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘My dear Mātali, harness the chariot with its team of a thousand "
"thoroughbreds. We will go to a park and see the scenery.’"

msgctxt "sn11.19:1.4"
msgid ""
"‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa "
"devānamindassa paṭissutvā sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā sakkassa "
"devānamindassa paṭivedesi:"
msgstr ""
"‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali. He harnessed the chariot and informed Sakka:"

msgctxt "sn11.19:1.5"
msgid "‘yutto kho te, mārisa, sahassayutto ājaññaratho."
msgstr ""
"‘Good sir, the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds has been "
"harnessed."

msgctxt "sn11.19:1.6"
msgid "Yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī’ti."
msgstr "Please go at your convenience.’"

msgctxt "sn11.19:1.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo vejayantapāsādā orohanto añjaliṃ "
"katvā sudaṃ bhagavantaṃ namassati."
msgstr ""
"Then Sakka descended from the Palace of Victory, raised his joined palms, "
"and revered the Buddha."

msgctxt "sn11.19:1.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "So Mātali the charioteer addressed Sakka in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.19:2.1"
msgid "‘Yañhi devā manussā ca,"
msgstr "‘Gods and men"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:2.2"
msgid "taṃ namassanti vāsava;"
msgstr "worship you, Vāsava."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:2.3"
msgid "Atha ko nāma so yakkho,"
msgstr "So what’s the name of the spirit"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:2.4"
msgid "yaṃ tvaṃ sakka namassasī’ti."
msgstr "that you worship, Sakka?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.505"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.19:3.1"
msgid "‘Yo idha sammāsambuddho,"
msgstr "‘It’s the fully awakened Buddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:3.2"
msgid "asmiṃ loke sadevake;"
msgstr "the Teacher of peerless name"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:3.3"
msgid "Anomanāmaṃ satthāraṃ,"
msgstr "in this world with its gods—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:3.4"
msgid "taṃ namassāmi mātali."
msgstr "that’s who I worship, Mātali."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.19:4.1"
msgid "Yesaṃ rāgo ca doso ca,"
msgstr "Those who have discarded"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:4.2"
msgid "avijjā ca virājitā;"
msgstr "greed, hate, and ignorance,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:4.3"
msgid "Khīṇāsavā arahanto,"
msgstr "the perfected ones with defilements ended—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:4.4"
msgid "te namassāmi mātali."
msgstr "they're who I worship, Mātali."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.19:5.1"
msgid "Ye rāgadosavinayā,"
msgstr "The trainees who take pleasure in decreasing suffering,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:5.2"
msgid "avijjāsamatikkamā;"
msgstr "diligently pursuing the training"

# See BB’s note on this. Given that the verse has five padas, it’s almost certain that there is textual corruption. Treating these as truncated datives is a kludge, but I can’t think of a better alternative.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:5.3"
msgid "Sekkhā apacayārāmā,"
msgstr "for getting rid of greed and hate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:5.4"
msgid "appamattānusikkhare;"
msgstr "and going past ignorance—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:5.5"
msgid "Te namassāmi mātalī’ti."
msgstr "they’re who I worship, Mātali.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.19:6.1"
msgid "‘Seṭṭhā hi kira lokasmiṃ,"
msgstr "‘Those who you worship"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:6.2"
msgid "ye tvaṃ sakka namassasi;"
msgstr "seem to be the best in the world, Sakka."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:6.3"
msgid "Ahampi te namassāmi,"
msgstr "I too will worship"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:6.4"
msgid "ye namassasi vāsavā’ti."
msgstr "those who you worship, Sakka.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.19:7.1"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna maghavā,"
msgstr "After saying this, Maghavā the chief,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:7.2"
msgid "devarājā sujampati;"
msgstr "king of gods, Sujā’s husband,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:7.3"
msgid "Bhagavantaṃ namassitvā,"
msgstr "having worshipped the Buddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.19:7.4"
msgid "pamukho rathamāruhī”ti."
msgstr "climbed into his chariot.”"
